document_data.History:
The ''conjure elemental'' spell was first introduced in the time of [[Netheril]], in [[-1728 DR|2131 NY (âˆ’1728 DR)]], under the name '''''Tipald's conjuration''''', after the [[arcanist]] [[Tipald]].

In the month of [[Eleasis]], of the {{YearlinkName|1371}}, the city of [[Ravens Bluff]]'s [[Ministry of Art]] and [[Wizards Guild]] jointly declared it illegal to cast ''conjure elemental'' within city limits due to a raging unnatural storm at the time called the [[Soulstorm]]. In addition to threatening arrest for those that broke this decree, it was declared that breaking this prohibition would result in a permanent expulsion from either organization.{{Cite trumpeter/2-8|2}}{{LCRB}}

''Conjure elemental'' was commonly known and used by the magical community by [[1358 DR]].
